2.Genomic Information

* DNA Mutation

(1) Yes : if occured mutation is one of the following variant types - Missense mutation, Nonsense mutation, Splice site, In-frame insertion, In-frame deletion, Frame-shift insertion, Frame-shift deletion

* RNA

(1) RNA high : z-score ≥ 1

(2) RNA low : z-score ≤ -1

* Proteome

(1) Proteome high : z-score ≥ 1.5

(2) Proteome low : z-score ≤ 0.5

3. Reference DB

1. Variant to Gene:

Database: DBSNP

Url: https://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/snp/

Source file:

File 1 - https://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/snp/organisms/human_9606_b151_GRCh38p7/VCF/00-All.vcf.gz

File 2 - https://ftp.ensembl.org/pub/release-106/gtf/homo_sapiens/Homo_sapiens.GRCh38.106.gtf.gz

Description:

Using two source files, linkage corresponding genetic information based on the mutation position

2. Gene to Disease:

Database: DisGeNET

Url: https://www.disgenet.org/

Source file:

https://www.disgenet.org/static/disgenet_ap1/files/downloads/curated_gene_disease_associations.tsv.gz

Description:

# Obtaining matching cancer disease information from genetic information

3. Disease to Pubmed counts:

Database: PubTator Central

Url: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/research/pubtator/

Source file:

https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/lu/PubTatorCentral/disease2pubtatorcentral.gz

Description:

Get top cancer diseases mentioned in PubMed (Maximum 15)

4. Disease to Drug:

Database: TTD (Therapeutic Target Database)

Url:http://db.idrblab.net/ttd/

Source file:

http://idrblab.net/ttd/sites/default/files/ttd_database/P1-05-Drug_disease.txt

Description:

Obtaining matching drug information from disease information

Filter only approved drug information from FDA
